pageTitle: Baker Takes Second at CSC Invite
textBeforeTable: Baker will next hit the links on Sept. 25-26 at the Firekeeper Golf Club in Mayetta, Kan., in its host Baker Invitational Tournament. The Wildcats finished ahead of Columbia College who finished third, fellow HAAC school Graceland who finished fourth, host school Culver-Stockton who took fifth and Quincy University finished sixth. Sophomore Emma Tinsley tied for 16th with her 191 total score and teammate Jade Brake rounded out the tournament for Baker with a score of 199. Freshman Rebecca Holder finished alone in 15th-place with an overall score of 190. She shot a first found score of 96 and improved by two shots in the second round with a score of 94. Baker finished just four shots back of first-place Ashford University. Morgan Miller tied for 10th-place with her two-round total of 184 with a first round score of 93 and second round score of 91. Freshman Lindsey Mateer highlighted the tourney with a second-place finish out of 28 golfers with a first round 83 and second round 85 for a two-round score of 168. QUINCY, Ill. – In its second meet of the Fall season, the Baker University women’s golf team finished second out of six teams at the Culver-Stockton Wildcat Invite at the Spring Lake Country Club in Quincy, Ill.
